race.comment: ALABAMA GIRL (9) Dundeel mare who comes up from Victoria and now in the Everson yard. Blinkers come off and the winkers go on after chipping away when fifth over 1607m at Kilmore on September 14. Can return to winning form. KAHLUA GIRL (1) set to peak fourth-up after the two sharp minor placings. Stuck on well in the heavy conditions when second as fav over 1190m at Grafton. Maps well and doesn't have to improve much to take this out. DAZZLING PEACE (6) sat up on the speed at debut when a tough winner over 1006m at Grafton. Has further improvement and gets map favours. CHILPUR (7) strengthened over the break, and this looks slightly easier after finishing fourth over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast. Winning rider back aboard and strips fitter. Something for the Multiples: ELLRO (8)
